The Nigerian Customs Service, Kano/Jigawa Area Command, has realized over N7.94 billion in the first half of the year 2019. Addressing newsmen in his office, the Area Controller Kano/Jigawa Command, Comptroller Nasir Ahmed, said the revenue was realized between January and June, 2019. “We have a target of  N14.6bn for the year under review and what we have realized so far is N939m and this represents 54.32 per cent of our total target,” he said. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE Mr Ahmed called on business partners to be more compliant as the command expects better performance. Meanwhile, the Kano/Jigawa Area Command has impounded three containers of imported vegetable cooking oil worth millions of naira. Customs impound rice worth N100m in Jigawa Customs release 11 Hilux vans, conceal owner’s identity Customs intercepts rolls of tramadol in Kano Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin